englishTranslation: He is not my enemy! He is my boyfriend!

spanishExample: ¡Termina este trabajo! Lo tenías que terminar ayer.
englishTranslation: Finish this work! You had to finish it yesterday.

spanishExample: Mi enemigo es tonto, pero no es un asesino.
englishTranslation: My enemy is dumb, but he isn’t a murderer.

spanishExample: Mi tía dice que si siguen será duro.
englishTranslation: My aunt says that if they continue it will be hard.

spanishExample: Mi tía me dijo que soy un idiota por no escuchar a mi abuela.
englishTranslation: My aunt told me I’m an idiot for not listening to my grandmother.

spanishExample: Mi tío es el mejor humano del mundo.
englishTranslation: My uncle is the best human in the world.

spanishExample: Mi tío tiene un auto negro que le gusta.
englishTranslation: My uncle has a black car that he likes.

spanishExample: No terminé, así que sigo hablando con mi abuela.
englishTranslation: I didn’t finish, so I continue talking to my grandmother.

spanishExample: Qué increíble que mi novia y su abuelo sigan hablando.
englishTranslation: How incredible that my girlfriend and her grandfather continue talking.

spanishExample: Si me sigues llamando un asesino, voy a estar triste.
englishTranslation: If you keep calling me a murderer, I’m going to be sad.

spanishExample: Si termino esto, el animal puede ser libre.
englishTranslation: If I finish this, the animal can be free.

spanishExample: Sigue creyendo que su marido no es un idiota.
englishTranslation: She keeps believing her husband isn’t an idiot.

spanishExample: Sigue hablando con tu novia porque ella es especial.
englishTranslation: Keep talking to your girlfriend because she is special.

spanishExample: Su marido quiere ver los animales.
englishTranslation: Her husband wants to see the animals.

spanishExample: Terminamos nuestro trabajo y mi novio terminará el suyo pronto.
englishTranslation: We finished our work and my boyfriend will finish his soon.
